CDC testing guidelines have been updated again to say if you are a close contact of someone with COVID and don't have symptoms, you NEED a test.

As I wrote in early Sept, America doesn't have a coherent strategy for asymptomatic testing. It needs one.
https://t.co/5cfYHAPff3

My latest: The controversy over the CDC testing guideline change last week was just a symptom of a deeper problem: this far into the pandemic, America doesn't have a coherent strategy for asymptomatic testing.
